t: Psalm 132
A Song of degrees.
Lord,*sp remember David, and all his afflictions:
How*p he sware unto the Lord,*s and vowed unto the mighty God of Jacob;
Surely*p I will not come into the tabernacle of my house, nor go up into my bed;
I*p will not give sleep to mine eyes, or slumber to mine eyelids,
Until*p I find out a place for the Lord,*s an habitation for the mighty God of Jacob.
Lo,*p we heard of it at Ephratah: we found it in the fields of the wood.
We*p will go into his tabernacles: we will worship at his footstool.
Arise,*p O Lord,*s into thy rest; thou, and the ark of thy strength.
Let*p thy priests be clothed with righteousness; and let thy saints shout for joy.
For*p thy servant David's sake turn not away the face of thine anointed.
The*p Lord*s hath sworn in truth unto David; he will not turn from it; Of the fruit of thy body will I set upon thy throne.
If*p thy children will keep my covenant and my testimony that I shall teach them, their children shall also sit upon thy throne for evermore.
For*p the Lord*s hath chosen Zion; he hath desired it for his habitation.
This*p is my rest for ever: here will I dwell; for I have desired it.
I*p will abundantly bless her provision: I will satisfy her poor with bread.
I*p will also clothe her priests with salvation: and her saints shall shout aloud for joy.
There*p will I make the horn of David to bud: I have ordained a lamp for mine anointed.
His*p enemies will I clothe with shame: but upon himself shall his crown flourish.
